        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 23 at 10:41PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1041 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Glenrio, or 21 miles south of Nara Visa, moving
southeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Glenrio.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
